{"title":"Horse Cycles Rambler Gravel Touring Bike","link":"https://theradavist.com/horse-cycles-rambler-gravel-touring-bike/","date":1727966047000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2500\" height=\"1666\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/RAMBLER_OUTSIDE-84.jpg?fit=1200,1666&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/RAMBLER_OUTSIDE-84.jpg?w=2500&amp;quality=75 2500w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/RAMBLER_OUTSIDE-84.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/RAMBLER_OUTSIDE-84.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/RAMBLER_OUTSIDE-84.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/RAMBLER_OUTSIDE-84.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/RAMBLER_OUTSIDE-84.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p><em>The <a href=\"https://www.horsebrand.co/bikes/rambler-steel-fork-bikebacking\" target=\"_blank\">Horse Cycles Rambler</a> ($2,950 frameset) made its debut here at The Radavist in the <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/aspen-ridge-bikepacking-no-sleep-til-salida/\" target=\"_blank\">Salida Bikepacking</a> story we posted up last week. A few commented on how good the bikes looked, and here it is, unloaded and in its shiny, ombré sunset fade paint job…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/2024_Aspen_Ridge_Bikepacking-33.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/2024_Aspen_Ridge_Bikepacking-33.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/2024_Aspen_Ridge_Bikepacking-33.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/2024_Aspen_Ridge_Bikepacking-33.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/2024_Aspen_Ridge_Bikepacking-33.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>The Rambler is a gravel bike built around control, durability and functionality. It comes standard with a steel fork (carbon fork optional), rack and water bottle mounts where you want them, and UDH rear dropouts. With clearance for 29 x 2.25″ tires, a 70.5º head angle, and 74/73º seat angle, it’s designed to be ridden on everything from hardpack to chunky stuff. It retails for $2,950 for frame and fork.</p>\n<p><img width=\"2299\" height=\"1532\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/RAMBLER-GEO-WITH-GRAPH.jpg?fit=1200,1532&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/RAMBLER-GEO-WITH-GRAPH.jpg?w=2299&amp;quality=75 2299w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/RAMBLER-GEO-WITH-GRAPH.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/RAMBLER-GEO-WITH-GRAPH.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/RAMBLER-GEO-WITH-GRAPH.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/RAMBLER-GEO-WITH-GRAPH.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/RAMBLER-GEO-WITH-GRAPH.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Check out more at <a href=\"https://www.horsebrand.co/bikes/rambler-steel-fork-bikebacking\" target=\"_blank\">Horse Cycles</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/horse-cycles-rambler-gravel-touring-bike/\">Horse Cycles Rambler Gravel Touring Bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"ef30b95a1ab974b827b8788bd12cab587aa2a7273ec8ebdaa15a0c4f937eca63","category":"Cycling"}